==English==
===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Victor Grignard|François Auguste Victor Grignard]], a Nobel Prize-winning French chemist.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Grignard]] [[reagent]]'''
#{{chemistry}} an [[alkyl]] or [[aryl]] [[magnesium]] [[halide]], used in the [[Grignard reaction]] to form [[substituted]] [[alcohol]]s; they are formed from alkyl or aryl halides and [[metallic]] magnesium

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[Grignardin reagenssi]]

